<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 19 at 8:48AM MST  by NWS Missoula</headline>
<description>...Intense snow showers will impact portions of central Flathead
County through 1000 AM MST...
At 847 AM MST, the public reported a line of intense snow showers
extending from 6 miles east of West Glacier to 10 miles southwest of
Whitefish. These showers were nearly stationary.  Expect one inch
per hour snow rates under this band, creating very low visibility
and quickly covering highway 2 in the area.
HAZARD...Visibility one-half mile or less.
SOURCE...Public.
IMPACT...Low visibility could result in dangerous driving
conditions.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
